Classes in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.power.models used by org.cloudbus.cloudsim.power.models
PowerModel
          The PowerModel interface needs to be implemented in order to provide a model of power consumption depending on utilization for system components.
PowerModelSpecPower
          The abstract class of power models created based on data from SPECpower benchmark: http://www.spec.org/power_ssj2008/ If you are using any algorithms, policies or workload included in the power package, please cite the following paper: Anton Beloglazov, and Rajkumar Buyya, "Optimal Online Deterministic Algorithms and Adaptive Heuristics for Energy and Performance Efficient Dynamic Consolidation of Virtual Machines in Cloud Data Centers", Concurrency and Computation: Practice and Experience (CCPE), Volume 24, Issue 13, Pages: 1397-1420, John Wiley & Sons, Ltd, New York, USA, 2012
